NAME
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities - create and manage Google
        Binary Authorization Attestation Authorities

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities GROUP | COMMAND
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Create and manage Google Binary Authorization Attestation
    Authorities.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

GROUPS
    GROUP is one of the following:

     public-keys
        (ALPHA) Create and manage public keys associated with Attestation
        Authorities.

COMMANDS
    COMMAND is one of the following:

     add-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Add IAM policy binding to an authority.

     create
        (ALPHA) Create an Attestation Authority.

     delete
        (ALPHA) Delete an Attestation Authority.

     describe
        (ALPHA) Describe an Attestation Authority.

     get-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Get the IAM policy for an authority.

     list
        (ALPHA) List Attestation Authorities associated with the current
        project.

     remove-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Remove IAM policy binding to an authority.

     set-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Set the IAM policy for an authority.

     update
        (ALPHA) Update an existing Attestation Authority.

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. Usually, users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply
    for access, agree to applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted.
    Contact Google or sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product
    pages can be found at https://cloud.google.com/products/.

